WHISK eggs together in medium bowl and scramble over medium heat. Season to taste with salt and black pepper. LAYER one-fourth eggs, 3 slices bacon and 1/4 cup seasoned cheese on each of 4 bread slices. Close with remaining bread slices. SPREAD butter on top and bottom of sandwiches; grill in two-sided tabletop grill for 3 to 5 minutes or until golden and cheese is melted. SPRINKLE 2 tablespoons cheese over top of each sandwich and heat briefly to melt. SLICE each sandwich in half diagonally.